From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Subject: [PATCH] phy: sun4i-usb: force OTG peripheral (usb-proxy appliance)

The Orange Pi Zero micro-USB OTG ID pin reads as host, so the phy reroutes
the port to the EHCI host controller and the musb gadget never enumerates on
the upstream host. This board is only ever a USB gadget, so always report id
as peripheral. Mirrors what the Armbian kernel does downstream.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
--- a/drivers/phy/allwinner/phy-sun4i-usb.c	2026-06-25 20:43:33
+++ b/drivers/phy/allwinner/phy-sun4i-usb.c	2026-06-25 20:43:33
@@ -402,6 +402,14 @@
 
 static int sun4i_usb_phy0_get_id_det(struct sun4i_usb_phy_data *data)
 {
+	/*
+	 * usb-proxy appliance: the micro-USB OTG port is wired only as a USB
+	 * gadget (the upstream-host link); devices to proxy use the EHCI/OHCI
+	 * USB-A ports. The OTG ID pin reads as host on this board, which makes
+	 * the phy reroute the port to the host controller and the gadget never
+	 * enumerates. Force peripheral by always reporting id as high.
+	 */
+	return 1;
 	switch (data->dr_mode) {
 	case USB_DR_MODE_OTG:
 		if (data->id_det_gpio)
